overview: The user initiated a project to build a sleep questionnaire
  application, requiring a database for responses, an admin dashboard for data
  access, and authentication. After evaluating the existing codebase, a plan was
  developed to implement a QuestionnaireResponse model in Prisma, create API
  routes for data submission and retrieval (including CSV export), and build a
  simple admin dashboard. A key decision involved using a simple password-based
  authentication system, which was later refined to utilize Next.js middleware
  for cleaner route protection. The implementation was thoroughly tested,
  confirming that database saving, data fetching, CSV export, and the
  authentication flow (login, logout, and middleware protection) were all fully
  functional.
